Hi Evmos community. It is good to be posting here! I am getting ready to launch ERC-20 token $PAGE (bridged via Gravity Bridge) into Evmos as an ERC-20 token. More information about PageDAO can be found at https://pagedao.org. At this point, we need to be sure that the json is correct. In my mind the main question that remains is the exponent of 8; which we have done to attempt to match the Ethereum token (it has 8 decimal places). As long as that is correct, I believe we should be good to go!

Our one sentence description: What is Page: Page is a cryptocurrency built with the needs of writers in mind, designed to incentivize the growth of open source publishing technology for Web3 environments.

Here is our bridge txn data:

{"key":"denom","value":"ibc/E1136B918D1D8CD8ADAA7C6B73A98588AE28F2A3E1F89FD2DC4E5FB7D8CA1E82"}

